			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/pet hold is like /pet guard here.  The pet will stay in "held" mode.  I make it a point of doing a /pet back off right before I do a pet attack, and even included a /pet back off right after the /pet hold.  The hold freezes the pet, but does NOT prevent things from getting on its hate list, /pet back off wipes it.  Now while I think I'll remove /pet back off from the hold key, I do believe I'll leave it on my attack, so I can guarantee that Kuddles will go after the mob I want, at least for a little while.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Venerable Zanros Farwanderer</span> Iksar Feral Lord of Chaotic Rampage, Stromm Server
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Venerable Zarros Livinglight</span> High Elven Archon, Guildless on Saryrn
<br />

<br />
"Raid? No thanks, don't care for it."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
