			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/pet hold is just a switch to turn off combat for your pet.
<br />

<br />
Contrary to what others have said above, your pet will NOT follow you around - if you've /pet sit or /pet guarded him he/she will, respectively, stand there or return to his/her guard point.  Otherwise he/she will follow you around.  Yes I'm being nitpicky.
<br />

<br />
The most important thing to note about /pet hold is that unlike /pet backoff it does not clear its aggro list, thus you still need the latter to fully control your pet.  This is extremely useful however (that its aggro list is not cleared) and I recommend highly to not combine the two in one hotkey.  ymmv.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
