				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/pet hold is just a switch to turn off combat for your pet. 
<br />

<br />
Contrary to what others have said above, your pet will NOT follow you around - if you've /pet sit or /pet guarded him he/she will, respectively, stand there or return to his/her guard point. Otherwise he/she will follow you around. Yes I'm being nitpicky</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I found that a little confusing.  Though I'm sure Gronker meant it the same way I'm going to say it, I'm going to rephrase to make it clearer.
<br />

<br />
If you hit /pet hold, your warder will stop attacking and act as if it had no aggro. (It still has aggro, but won't act on it until you release it from /pet hold by issuing an attack command.)
<br />

<br />
If you have the warder set to /pet sit, then it will stop fighting and stay right where it is, even though the mob is beating on it.
<br />

<br />
If you have the warder set to /pet guard here, then it will stop fighting and walk back to the guard spot, and the mob will follow along, making this a great way to position summoning mobs.
<br />

<br />
If your pet is normally following you, then it will walk back to you when you /pet hold, bringing the mob in tow.
<br />

<br />
Note that if you do /pet hold, then tell the warder to attack something new, it will probably ignore the new mob and go back to fighting the one it was on when you did the /pet hold. It still has a lot of aggro on that mob, you see, and the /pet attack command cancels /pet hold. That's why it's a good idea to /pet back off when you /pet hold, to clear the warder's aggro too.
<br />

<br />
I hope that's clear.<br />_________________<br /><br><div align=center><img src="http://www.shootingiron.com/tipop/notherkrag.jpg" width="500" height="200" border="0" usemap="#nothermap"><map name="nothermap"><area alt="Fury of Faith" coords="31,157,152,187" href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/fury"><area alt="Tipop's Homepage" coords="186,157,321,187"  href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/"><area alt="Kraggan's Magelo Profile" coords="342,157,465,186" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120506"></map></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
