			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, I find it much better to combine a backoff and attack as opposed to hold and back off.
<br />

<br />
The pet can still accumulate hate while on hold, and without clearing that hate immediately before attacking, the pet will decide who to attack based on stored hate.  I skip backoff after a hold, as I really don't care what his current hate is, so long as I automatically clear hate before the attack.  This also means that I can one button toggle targets for my pet without much issue saving me time.
<br />

<br />
Hot key button 1:
<br />
/pet back off
<br />
/pet attack
<br />

<br />
Hot key button 2:
<br />
/pet hold
<br />

<br />
That's all I need.  Note there is no need to pause between commands on button 1.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110634" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Isilm</a>
<br />
Dysfunctional Lizard Beastlord and sidekick Fluffy
