				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Akiea wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Heres a scenario:
<br />

<br />
Im in ME fighting 4 Arms and get three on the pull I slow all and start trying to take them out one by one. Now, I have them all hitting me so keeping Fluffy on one particular mob isnt a problem until pet push places the mob far enough out for the other two to hit my pet. At this point my stupid pet always wants to change targets to whats hitting it rather than what I want it to attack(Maybe your pets a bit smarter but mines stupid like that no treat for joo Fluffy!) 
