				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No way... sorry to disappoint you but if you hit /pet hold while pet killing 1 mob, fluffy will just end up dying an horrible death and wouldnt even have defended itself... 
<br />

<br />
when do i see /pet hold being usefull :
<br />
- AE spells during raids : this one is obvious, sometimes you just have to wait and get no agro on some mobs this is what can help
<br />
- Crowd control : i rarely group with peeps that can lull/pac mobs, so when mobs get into camp there are often many. Pet hold allow me to chose where each mob will be parked : send fluffy on some mob, get on the other, wait that other mob taken care by fluffy get  rooted, /pet hold, then take care of next one untill you get all root and parked as you like. Nothing more annoying than a pet proc breaking root each round and pet who doesnt want to just /back off ... 
<br />
- Wall *poofing* : i like this one too, when you fight a mob in some zones you cant really avoid mobs to be pushed back into walls, and sometimes this will cause them to poof and bring back some trains... once more /back off just doesnt do it sometimes... /pet hold, pets just gets back to what it was doing (/pet guard me for me usually) and mob slowly slides off the wall beating on fluffy untill you kick /pet kill (i prefer kill than attack sorry :p)
<br />
- Most usual one and obvious too : pulling... you pull get hit a few times, and when you get back to camp you cross fluffy charging like a freak... so if you dont like to spam your group mates with /pet backoff its what you need.
<br />

<br />
I believe ive covered all my uses for it <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> and i hope you're now convinced how cool it is hehe, just not for what you want though... 
<br />

<br />
B
<br />

<br />
PS - when i started my first pet class (a magi) i thought /pet as you were prevented me from pet keeping agro list but it doesnt. So i'm still wondering what this command as for use, if you guys got inputs i'm up hehe<br />_________________<br />Boosty from Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
