			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I see the
<br />

<br />
/pet hold
<br />
/pet back off
<br />

<br />
bit all the time.  And frankly, it's boggling to me.  Logically it makes much more sense to place /pet back off on the same key as /pet attack (immediately before).  Your pet STILL has his hate list cleared, and now you have a nifty key that can reorient your pet with a single keystroke in the middle of a fight.
<br />

<br />
It seems that at one point, a person that played a mage (mostly a point pet and med between nukes class) figured gee, here's an idea.  The idea got written to a guide, and the guide became gospel.
<br />

<br />
I can't say I've ever seen definatively that pet hold freezes the hate list, though it definately sets pet to non-aggressive.  Yet, moving that pet back off to the attack key neatly steps around the problem and works in either case.
<br />

<br />
I suppose if you really wanted to be anal, you could place /pet back off in both attack and hold keys, but that's rather overkill.
<br />

<br />
Just my two cents.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110634" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Isilm</a>
<br />
Dysfunctional Lizard Beastlord and sidekick Fluffy
<br />
65.80...  Warning: Tanking Arch Mage in Fire has been deemed hazardous to your health.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
